[SN]TITLE[SN]
Car worth £19,000 stolen from St Boswells garage

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A car worth £19,000 has been stolen from a yard at the back of a garage in the Scottish Borders.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The white Ford Focus RS, registration number SL59 HVF, was taken from Lawries Garage at St Boswells at 02:30 on Thursday.
The vehicle was driven north and was spotted in the Edinburgh area some time later.
Anyone who saw anything suspicious or may have seen the car being driven has been asked to contact police.
